snippet.title: Amber Kamminga - Name On It | OFFICIAL LYRIC VIDEO 2021
snippet.description:
This is my 3rd single, it's about serendipity. I had a lot of fun animating this lyric video on ProCreate so I hope you enjoy it! Text overlay by Hana Taragona. 

Produced by Nick Jongejan & Amber Kamminga, 2021.
Music by Amber Kamminga & Dave Neijsen.
Written by Amber Kamminga.
●
Listen on Spotify: https://open.spotify.com/track/6GbYnSyF50OAMQbzfb3zjn?si=fba9ae8ed3794006
Listen on Apple Music: https://music.apple.com/us/album/name-on-it/1587028481?i=1587028482
Say 'hi' on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/amberkamminga/
●
LYRICS:
Could see it coming from the start
Didn't make it any easier on my heart
We talk about work, and how's your family?
Heard you got someone out there replacing me

So I tell you "thanks for taking time to see me"
Tell my friends seeing you was easy
We're so glad, look at how good we're at being friends

We both moved on and we're better off
Speaking the truth would be good for no one
But let me be honest here
Still a part of my heart's got your name on it
If it wasn't so far from where I live
Your door would have my name on it

Played it cool, think you didn’t notice
All the time that I spent rehearsing this moment
Got close to telling you I was scared
That I'd cry seeing you again
Cause I hate the way we had to end
I choose to not say a thing but

"Thanks for taking time to see me"
Tell all my friends seeing you was easy
We're so glad, look how good we’re at being friends


We both moved on and we're better off
Speaking the truth would be good for no one
But let me be honest here
Still a part of my heart's got your name on it
If it wasn't so far from where I live
Your door would have my name on it
(It, it, it, it)
Would have my name on it
(It, it, it, it)

I'm reading in to (I'm reading in to)
The way you hold me (The way you hold me)
A little more than any old friend should
I'm staring in to your (I'm staring in to your)
Eyes that avoid me (Eyes that avoid me)
A little longer than any one else would

But we both moved on and we’re better off
Speaking the truth, it won’t be good for our hearts
No point in making clear
That a part of my heart's got your name on it
Maybe over time it won't be half as big, no
We both moved on and we're better off
Speaking the truth would be good for no one
But let me be honest here
Still a part of my heart's got your name on it
If it wasn't so far from where I live
Your door would have my name on it
(It, it, it, it)
Would have my name on it
(It, it, it, it)
Would have my name on it
(It, it, it, it)
Would have my name on it
(It, it, it, it)
Would have my name on it
